text.section:
The Commission consists of the following 12 members:
the Attorney General;
the Secretary of General Services;
the Secretary of Budget and Management; and
the following nine members appointed by the Governor with the advice and consent of the Senate:
two members of the public who are not directly employed in the field of corrections;
two correctional personnel from State government;
two correctional personnel from local government;
one official or employee of a national correctional accreditation organization;
one elected official from a local governing body; and
one member who is licensed, certified, or registered by the State as a mental health or medical professional.
